<br>
Companies should go for their labor where it is cheapest.  That is their duty in a capitalist country.  Anything else is a failure to live up to their obligations to the shareholders.  It increases the profits of the shareholders, so thus increases the amount of money flowing into the American economy.<br>
<br>
Failure to make choices leading to greatest profitability make a company non competitive and represent a failure of the management to discharge its duties in good faith.<br>
