<br>
Ideally, a stratification will become increasingly evident.  However, the stratification should be based on merit (a combination of talent and work ethic, basically productivity) and not on birth right, race, religion, etc.<br>
<br>
Those jobs moving south of the border are jobs the US should be trying to outsource anyways.  It's better for the country as a whole even if it's locally bad.  We should be trying to increase high paying skilled jobs and decrease mindless factory jobs.  This is the way of the future.  Over time, more and more factory jobs will be replaced not by Mexicans but by machines.  This increases our GNP and the productivity of our country, as well as the average standard of living.<br>
<br>
Don't try to stand in the way of progress, it will just laugh at you and keep on going.<br>
